legend bottom
  == Automated test coverage ==
  |= Node |= Meaning |= Where |
  |<back:#BFE3C6> green </back>| End-to-end (Playwright) | frontend/e2e/*.spec.ts |
  |<back:#F6E1B0> amber </back>| Built, unit/component only -> <b>remaining e2e backlog</b> | frontend/src/**/*.test.tsx |
  |<back:#F3C9C4> red </back>| No automated test (mostly not-yet-built) | -- |
  |<back:#E4E4E4> grey </back>| Backend, pytest-covered, out of frontend-e2e scope | tests/ (pytest) |
  <b>Now covered:</b> the guardian console (sign-in, profiles, intake, queue, review,
  send-back, and the ADR-005 <b>Approve</b> gate), the child-initiated story
  request loop (WS-B: request, approve/decline, proposed series, anchored
  continuations), and the reader 409-conflict reconciliation all have
  Playwright coverage; Approve, the authored-request path, and a naive-kid
  misuse scenario also have real-backend smoke tests (e2e-real/*.spec.ts,
  zero mocks).
  <b>Remaining amber:</b> "Avatar shows new story ready!" pill state is asserted
  in Vitest only, not e2e.
  <b>Not yet recolored on this backbone (INTERIM):</b> the ADR-014 device-grant /
  AdultGate steps and the WS-J admin surfaces (user management #267, authoring
  queue #268, moderation dashboard/thresholds, provider allowlist) now have their
  own e2e specs (listed above), but this journey's step nodes have not been
  re-drawn to include them. Treat this map as current only for the
  request -> approve -> read loop it depicts.
endlegend

